ted protein kinase and increasing expression of zonula occludens-1. CONCLUSIONS: Enteric glial cells from patients with CD have reduced production of 15-HETE, which controls IEB permeability by inhibiting adenosine monophosphate-activated protein kinase and increasing expression of zonula occludens-1.},
